President Barack Obama has proclaimed April 9, 2014, as National Former Prisoner of War Recognition Day. On this day, Americans are encouraged to honor all American prisoners of war, service members, and veterans. The proclamation recognizes the sacrifices made by these individuals and their families, who have endured physical and mental torture, starvation, and isolation. It also calls for the fulfillment of the responsibility to care for these heroes and their families. The proclamation encourages the observance of this day through appropriate ceremonies and activities by federal, state, and local government officials and organizations.